answers.body_markdown:
The return type must be determined at compile-time. You might use [`std::common_type`](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/types/common_type) (since C++11):

&gt; For arithmetic types not subject to promotion, the common type may be viewed as the type of the (possibly mixed-mode) arithmetic expression such as `T0() + T1() + ... + Tn()`.

    template &lt; typename T, typename X&gt;
    typename std::common_type&lt;T, X&gt;::type Max_Number ( T valueA, X valueB ) {
        ...
    }

Or use [`std::conditional`](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/types/conditional) (since C++11) to declare the return type as the big one (whose `sizeof` is greater).

    template &lt; typename T, typename X&gt;
    typename std::conditional&lt;sizeof(T) &gt;= sizeof(X), T, X&gt;::type Max_Number ( T valueA, X valueB ) {
        ...
    }

Note that for this case, if `T` and `X` have the same size, `T` will always be used as the return type. If you want to control it more precisely, you can use some traits to specify the exact type.

Here is an example solution with [`std:: variant`][1]

    template &lt; typename T, typename X&gt; 
    std::variant&lt;T, X&gt;  Max_Number ( T valueA, X valueB )
    {
        std::variant&lt;T, X&gt; res;
        if ( valueA &gt; valueB ) 
           res = valueA; 
        else 
           res = valueB; 
        return res;
    }


  [1]: https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/utility/variant

The *[Trailing return](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/function)* with a *[conditional operator](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/operator_other#Conditional_operator)* is another way to go, which is available since [tag:C++11].

**([See online live](https://wandbox.org/permlink/wXnJzPDb5kQy4ty7))**


```c+ +
template &lt;typename T, typename X&gt;
constexpr auto Max_Number(T valueA, X valueB)-&gt; decltype(valueA &gt; valueB ? valueA : valueB)
{
	return valueA &gt; valueB ? valueA : valueB;
}
```

----------


See some advantages of using trailing return type here: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/52103775/advantage-of-using-trailing-return-type-in-c11-functions

